        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 9:52PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 952 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mannboro, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small trees and blow around
unsecured objects. Wind impacting handling of high profile
vehicles. Reduced visibility and minor flooding possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Chester and Chesterfield Court House around 1015 PM EDT.
Bellwood around 1020 PM EDT.
Richmond and Bensley around 1025 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include North Wellville,
Wayside, Richmond Heights, Addison, Ammon, Mountcastle, Elko,
Montrose, Sandston, and Glendale.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
